to one's surprise

This matter is important.

这件事情是重要的。

He eats too much so he has a stomachache.

他吃太多了所以胃痛。

options.voiceText: He eats too much so he has a stomachache.

My foot was hurt when I played football.

我踢足球时脚受伤了。

options.text: My foot was hurt when I played football.
options.voiceText: My foot was hurt when I played football.

subContents.content:
I can't move my neck.

我的脖子不能动了。

It is foolish to swim on a full stomach.

吃饱饭去游泳是愚蠢的。

options.text: It is foolish to swim on a full stomach.
options.voiceText: It is foolish to swim on a full stomach.

subContents.content:
My dad has a fever.

我爸爸发烧了。

Lie down flat and breathe deeply.

平躺下，深呼吸。

options.text: Lie down flat and breathe deeply.
options.voiceText: Lie down flat and breathe deeply.

subContents.content:

我认为你应该躺下。

options.text: I think you should lie down.
options.voiceText: I think you should lie down.

subContents.content:
I think you should rest.

我认为你应该休息。

He has a bad cough.

他咳嗽的很严重。

When will I know the result of my X-ray?

我何时可以知道X光检查的结果？

options.text: When will I know the result of my X-ray?
options.voiceText: When will I know the result of my X-ray?

subContents.content:
The boy has a toothache.

那个男孩牙痛。

analysisList.text: 这位老人不能忍受牙痛。

subContents.content:
Please help him take his temperature.

请帮他量体温。

options.text: Please help him take his temperature.
options.voiceText: Please help him take his temperature.

subContents.content:
He takes a break under the tree.

他在树下休息。

options.text: He takes a break under the tree.
options.voiceText: He takes a break under the tree.

analysisList.text: 我们三点半再休息一次。

subContents.content:
The passengers get on the bus.

乘客们上车。

options.text: The passengers get on the bus.
options.voiceText: The passengers get on the bus.

analysisList.text: 所有乘客都下了公交车。

subContents.content:
He was off his seat.

他离开他的位子。

The passengers get off the bus.

乘客们下车。

options.text: The passengers get off the bus.
options.voiceText: The passengers get off the bus.

subContents.content:
To my surprise, the boy wears a dress.

使我惊讶的是那个男孩穿了一条裙子。

options.text: To my surprise, the boy wears a dress.
options.voiceText: To my surprise, the boy wears a dress.

analysisList.text: 我感到惊奇的是这个计划成功了。

subContents.content:
The boy climbed onto the roof top.

男孩朝屋顶爬去。

options.text: The boy climbed onto the roof top.
options.voiceText: The boy climbed onto the roof top.

对我来说做饭是一个问题。

options.text: Cooking dinner is a trouble for me.
options.voiceText: Cooking dinner is a trouble for me.

subContents.content:
The father hit his son.

那位爸爸打他的儿子。

Could you cook a meal right away?

你能马上做点饭吗？

options.text: Could you cook a meal right away?
options.voiceText: Could you cook a meal right away?

analysisList.text: 我会立刻把这本书给您寄去。
